                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is not really a problem.\r\n\r\nYou are setting to each element a own translation object.\r\nThere is no way for an element to detect if the same object has already been set to another element nor could it use this object as the elements have no connection to each other.\r\n\r\nAs generic and documented solution you should simply set a default Translator to Zend_Form which is being used when the element has no instance set.\r\n\r\nSee Zend_Form::setDefaultTranslator().",
